Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of LDGM and compound codes for lossy source coding problems, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of sparse graphical codes and message-passing encoding, which are topics related to coding theory (cs.CC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses source coding with side information (the Wyner-Ziv problem) and channel coding with side information (the Gelfand-Pinsker problem), which are topics related to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
